docs.abstract: The United Nations Security Council discussed the recent protests in Iran over economic conditions there.
docs.snippet: The United Nations Security Council discussed the recent protests in Iran over economic conditions there.
docs.lead_paragraph: UNITED NATIONS — Efforts by the Trump administration to marshal a muscular international response to Iran’s crackdown on anti-government protesters appeared to backfire on Friday, as members of the United Nations Security Council instead used a special session called by the United States to lecture the American ambassador on the proper purpose of the body and to reaffirm support for the Iran nuclear agreement.

headline.main: The U.S. Wanted to Discuss Iran. Russia Brought Up Black Lives Matter.
headline.print_headline: Russia and U.S. Joust at U.N. Over Iran Protests

docs.abstract: The BlackRock chief plans to pressure companies to do more to cut carbon emissions, using the weight of his firm’s $9 trillion in assets.
docs.snippet: The BlackRock chief plans to pressure companies to do more to cut carbon emissions, using the weight of his firm’s $9 trillion in assets.
docs.lead_paragraph: The BlackRock chief’s annual letter to C.E.O.s is going out this morning and Andrew has a copy, which he writes about in his latest column. Mr. Fink’s letter has driven the conversation inside corporate America’s boardrooms for years — such as his proclamation that companies must have a purpose beyond profit, which preceded the Business Roundtable’s statement on stakeholder capitalism, and his call for corporate climate disclosures, which was followed by a raft of climate pledges by companies.

byline.original: By Andrew Ross Sorkin, Jason Karaian, Michael J. de la Merced, Lauren Hirsch and Ephrat Livni
